    "narrative": "Our primary offensive engine today features **Cal Raleigh** (78.02) and **Will Smith** (72.25), who both command the lineup thanks to favorable matchups against middling southpaws. **Cal Raleigh** benefits significantly from hitting second against Connor Prielipp, with his projection buoyed by a +8% order premium and a wind-aided park factor. Similarly, **Will Smith** draws a high-upside matchup against Chris Paddack; despite the \"lineup pending\" status, his projected presence in the three-hole, combined with a favorable wind blowing out, makes him an elite play. **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (66.83) rounds out our top-tier starters, as his inherent talent overrides the minor concerns of facing Steven Matz, bolstered further by the wind conditions providing a slight ceiling boost.\n\nIn the middle tier, we are treading carefully with **Daulton Varsho** (47.17), **Gavin Sheets** (44.66), **Jonathan Aranda** (42.70), and **Masyn Winn** (41.86). While these players are active, they are fighting against poor platoon splits or tough southpaw matchups. **Daulton Varsho** is a marginal start who is only included to maintain our competitive edge in the SB category; while his output is dampened by the presence of Ranger Suarez, his position in the #2 spot keeps him above our bench threshold. **Jonathan Aranda** and **Masyn Winn** remain high-risk plays today; **Aranda** struggles against Parker Messick\u2019s projected effectiveness, and **Winn** faces a slight downgrade due to wind blowing in at the stadium. \n\nBecause we are currently in a period of rotation for our deep bench\u2014which includes **Lawrence Butler**, **Geraldo Perdomo**, **Yainer Diaz**, **Tyler Freeman**, **Bryson Stott**, **Taylor Ward**, **Matt Chapman**, **Luis Arraez**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Gleyber Torres**, **Wenceel Perez**, and **Drew Gilbert**\u2014many of our bench assets are sidelined due to scheduled off-days. Given the thin roster availability for April 27th, there were no viable pivots today that could outperform the projected floor of our current starters. We are prioritizing the preservation of our limited game caps, keeping an eye on the official lineups to ensure **Will Smith** and others stay in their projected high-value spots.",
